{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Denis Odoi | image = Metall-Lokeren (5).jpg | fullname= Denis Frimpong Odoi<ref name="Retained List 2016-17">{{cite web |title=Retained List 2016–17 |url=https://www.efl.com/siteassets/efl-documents/efl-released-and-retained-list---2016-17.pdf |publisher=English Football League |format=PDF |accessdate=13 June 2017}}</ref> | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1988|5|27|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Leuven]], Belgium | height = 1.78 m | position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]] | currentclub = [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] | clubnumber = 4 | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 2006–2009 | clubs1 = [[Oud-Heverlee Leuven]] | caps1 = 58 | goals1 = 3 | years2 = 2009–2011 | clubs2 = [[K. Sint-Truidense V.V.|Sint-Truiden]] | caps2 = 70 | goals2 = 2 | years3 = 2011–2013 | clubs3 = [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]] | caps3 = 33 | goals3 = 0 | years4 = 2013–2016 | clubs4 = [[K.S.C. Lokeren Oost-Vlaanderen|Lokeren]] | caps4 = 95 | goals4 = 1 | years5 = 2016– | clubs5 = [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] | caps5 = 104 | goals5 = 3 | nationalyears1 = 2008 | nationalteam1 = [[Belgium national under-20 football team|Belgium U20]] | nationalcaps1 = 1 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | nationalyears2 = 2010 | nationalteam2 = [[Belgium national under-21 football team|Belgium U21]] | nationalcaps2 = 3 | nationalgoals2 = 0 | nationalyears3 = 2012– | nationalteam3 = [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] | nationalcaps3 = 1 | nationalgoals3 = 0 | club-update = 08:43, 10 February 2019 (UTC) | nationalteam-update = }} '''Denis Frimpong Odoi''' (born 27 May 1988) is a Belgian [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Premier League]] club [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.sporza.be/permalink/1.1013325 |title=Anderlecht snatches Odoi away from Sint-Truiden |language=dutch |date=29 April 2011 |publisher=sporza.be}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.sporza.be/permalink/1.1046497 |title=Odoi: "Standard did not show any respect" |language=dutch |date=17 June 2011 |publisher=sporza.be}}</ref> His father is from Ghana and his mother is from Belgium.
On 14 July 2016, it was announced that Odoi had signed for [[Football League Championship|English Championship]] side [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]]. Odoi signed for an undisclosed fee, signing a three-year contract with an option of a further 12 months.{{citation needed|date=August 2016}}
Odoi is a right-footed full-back who can operate on either side. He mainly played at left-back for the past 3 years for his former club, [[K.S.C. Lokeren Oost-Vlaanderen|Lokeren]]. He prefers playing centre back.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/fulham-denis-odoi-tomas-kalas-14399182.amp |title=Odoi: I've no idea whether I'll keep my starting spot |date=13 March 2018 |publisher=}}</ref>
==Fulham== On 5 August 2016, Odoi made his debut for [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] in a 1–0 win against [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]]- his debut drawing acclaim for his "outrageous display of skill" controlling the ball off of his back shoulder. <ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11681/10524689/fulhams-denis-odoi-with-outrageous-skill-off-his-back |title=Fulham's Denis Odoi with Outrageous Skill off His Back |language=english |date=6 August 2016 |publisher=skysports.com}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Fulham in a 3–2 win against [[Wigan Athletic]] on 11 February 2017.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/38865828 |title=Fulham 3–2 Wigan |publisher=BBC |date=11 February 2017 |accessdate=24 February 2017}}</ref>
In the summer of 2017 he nearly signed for [[AA Gent]] but stayed on an improved contract following intervention from the Fulham chairman's son.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sportwitness.co.uk/fulham-player-confirms-interest-another-club/ |title=Fulham player confirms interest from another club, glad chairman's son stopped move – Sport Witness |first=A. |last=E. |date=27 April 2018 |publisher=}}</ref> On 14 May 2018 he scored the winning goal as Fulham beat [[Derby County]] to reach the [[2018 EFL Championship play-off Final]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44026478 |title=Fulham 2–0 Derby County (Agg 2–1) |date=14 May 2018 |publisher= |via=www.bbc.co.uk}}</ref>
==International career== He made his senior Belgian debut in 2012.<ref>https://www.cottagersconfidential.sbnation.com/platform/amp/2016/7/14/12188408/denis-odoi-signs-from-lokeren</ref>
